<HEADLINE>
<P>
D'ARCY SANGER HAYMAN; FORMER HEAD OF UNESCO CULTURAL PLANNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 D'Arcy Sanger Hayman, 69, head of arts and cultural planning for UNESCO from 
1960 to 1980.An artist and teacher, she earned the rank of ambassador in the 
Paris-based position. She traveled to more than 100 member nations to set up 
projects and promote the arts for UNESCO. Among her books were "The Arts and 
Man" and "The Calculus Virgin." Her own art was exhibited in Brazil, England, 
France, Italy, Mexico and the United States. On June 19 in Los Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
