<P>
JUNE ANNA PETERSEN; PRODUCTION EXECUTIVE IN FILMS AND MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 June Anna Petersen, 45, production executive in films and music whose credits 
included "Beetlejuice" and "Stop Making Sense."A native of Denmark, she worked 
in Washington, D.C., before moving to Los Angeles in 1977. Ms. Petersen began 
her Hollywood career in United Artists' development section and later was 
assistant or associate producer to several film and music producers, including 
Jonathan Demme, David Byrne, James Foley and Tim Burton. While helping to 
organize the estate of the late Roy Orbison, she produced his final music video 
and initiated development of a film script about his life. On July 6 in Vero 
Beach, Fla., of colon and liver cancer. 
