<P>
PRINCESS FAIZA FOUAD RAUF; SOCIALITE, SISTER OF EGYPT'S LAST KING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Princess Faiza Fouad Rauf, 70, Beverly Hills socialite and sister of Egypt's 
last monarch. Mrs. Rauf was the sister of the late King Farouk, who abdicated 
when Egypt became a republic.During her life in Egypt, Mrs. Rauf entertained 
heads of state and was a key leader of the Red Crescent Society, the Moslem 
corollary of the Red Cross. In 1954, she moved to Istanbul and then Paris 
before settling in Beverly Hills, where she lived for 30 years. Popular at 
Westside charity events, the divorced Mrs. Rauf was linked romantically with 
Ali Khan and others, but never remarried. Announced on Thursday in Westwood. 
</P>
