<P>
YOUTH CHARGED IN SLAYING OF MOTORIST WHO RAN INTO GIRL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 16-year-old boy was charged Thursday with murder and armed robbery in the 
attack on a motorist who was beaten, robbed and shot to death by a mob when he 
got out of his car to check on a girl he had just hit. 
</P>
<P>
 Metro-Dade police Detective Marie Duboulay said authorities have not 
determined whether the 16-year-old was the gunman. "There are other people 
involved," she said. "We don't know how many more are involved." 
</P>
<P>
 Charles Bells, 44, went to check on Victoria Williams after the 11-year-old 
darted in front of his car Tuesday. She was not seriously hurt. Witnesses said 
a mob surrounded Bells, who was beaten with fists and a bottle and then shot. 
</P>
