<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FINALS; SPOTLIGHT; SINNER TO A SAINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jornal do Brasil in Rio de Janeiro 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "In the second half, Brazil prayed. . . . At that moment, all that was missing 
was one simple goal.The Swedes closed ranks in defense in a clear attempt to 
send the game to a decision by penalty kicks. In normal times, we ought to 
respect the weak. But that little dance by the goalie (Thomas) Ravelli, 
laughing at the television cameras, was demonic. Little Saint Romario's goal 
off a cross-field pass by the latter day sinner Jorginho brought to mind once 
again the phrase by which some people have grown accustomed to the good and bad 
things of life: God is Brazilian." 
</P>
