WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FINALS; SPOTLIGHT; A TIP OF THE CAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL DWYRE and WILLIAM D. MONTALBANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 From coast to coast, the cops have been great during this World Cup.In 
Foxboro, Mass., they stood on the field and saluted the flags of the competing 
countries while their anthems played. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Meadowlands, the New Jersey State police never abandoned their 
long-sleeved blue woolen shirts, despite the oppressive heat, nor did they ever 
turn away from their crowd-watching to sneak a peek at the field. Nor did the 
cops in Orlando waver from their crowd-watching duties, but in the wild 
evenings at Church Street Station, they were good sports until the wee hours, 
smiling at attempts to steal their OPD (Orlando Police Department) caps. BILL 
DWYRE and WILLIAM D. MONTALBANO 
</P>
