<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; RAMS; LEFT TACKLE A SORE SPOT WITHOUT ROOKIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With rookie Wayne Gandy still unsigned, Coach Chuck Knox might be looking for 
volunteers at left tackle. 
</P>
<P>
 Gandy is projected as the starter there, a key position because the tackle 
will protect oft-injured quarterback Chris Miller's blind side. * 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams signed backup quarterback T.J. Rubley and cornerback Wymon Henderson 
to one-year contracts, and tight end Travis McNeal agreed to terms on a 
one-year deal. MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
