<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; RELEASE POSSIBLY SIGNALS END FOR 
BROOKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Kansas City Royals released outfielder Hubie Brooks, who possibly ends his 
14-year, 1,645-game career. The lifetime .269 hitter spent most of his career 
in the National League, including 1990 with the Dodgers. Brooks, who was with 
the Angels in 1992, had 14 hits in 61 at-bats for the Royals this season after 
making the team as a nonroster invitee. . . . Colorado catcher Joe Girardi was 
put on the 15-day disabled list, retroactive to Monday, because of inflammation 
in his left patellar tendon. 
</P>
