<TEXT>
<P>
 The starting time for the closing ceremony that precedes the World Cup final 
between Italy and Brazil on Sunday at the Rose Bowl has been changed to 11:15 
a.m. from 11:45. 
</P>
<P>
 FIFA, the world governing body of soccer, requested the earlier start in order 
to give the players enough time to properly warm up for the game, which is 
scheduled to start at 12:35 p.m. 
