<TEXT>
<P>
 Retail Sales Rise: The U.S. Commerce Department said sales staged a recovery 
in June, rising 0.6%, after dropping for two months.The increase was about what 
economists had predicted. The turnaround was led by durable goods, particularly 
cars and building materials. Retail sales had dropped a revised 0.4% in May -- 
double a month-old 0.2% estimate -- and 1% in April. Those figures were taken 
as evidence that the rapid economic growth the nation experienced in late 1993 
has slowed to a more moderate pace. 
</P>
