<TEXT>
<P>
 U.S. Studios Fire Back in Britain: United International Pictures, the joint 
distribution arm of Universal Pictures, Paramount Pictures and 
Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer, has released a study to blunt recent criticism that major 
U.S. studios suck too much money out of the British economy, pay too little in 
taxes and don't contribute enough to the British film industry. The study by 
London Economics says critics have overstated film royalties sent to the United 
States by 300% and overstated UIP's British theatrical revenue by 1,400%. The 
study says taxes on royalties are consistent with British law. 
</P>
