<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HOME INVADERS BIND, BEAT, ROB FAMILY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robbers tied up a Santa Ana family at home Wednesday night and escaped with 
money, jewelry and the family's Mercedes, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The robbers ransacked the apartment as Se Touch and Lap Ko and their five 
children were held on the floor at gunpoint, said Sgt. Dick Faust. 
</P>
<P>
 The family told police the robbers numbered two to four. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was seriously injured, and the car was recovered undamaged in Midway 
City, Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 Touch, 60, came home from visiting a neighbor downstairs shortly after 8 p.m. 
to find his family tied up and robbers going through the apartment, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 He was pistol-whipped and then bound too, Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 The value of the stolen property was unknown. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 150 home-invasion robberies have been reported in Santa Ana, Garden 
Grove and Westminster since 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 Most are carried out by Asian or Latino gangs, police say. Immigrant families 
often are targeted in the belief that they keep money and valuables at home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
