<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; FBI ARRESTS DOCTOR ON FRAUD CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 49-year-old doctor suspected of defrauding a medical insurance company in 
Minnesota of more than $40,000 was arrested at his practice by FBI agents, 
officials said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Nagesh Shetty of Huntington Beach was released on his own recognizance 
Wednesday after appearing before a U.S. magistrate in Santa Ana.He faces 28 
counts of mail fraud, FBI spokesman Gary Morley said. 
</P>
<P>
 Shetty was arrested Tuesday at Harbor Newport Medical Center in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 A federal grand jury in Minneapolis returned an indictment on June 7, alleging 
that Shetty mailed fraudulent insurance claims to Blue Cross-Blue Shield of 
Minnesota for nonexistent, medically unnecessary or excessive medical 
treatment. 
</P>
<P>
 The indictment also alleges that over a nine-month period beginning in 
January, 1993, Shetty submitted numerous fraudulent health insurance claims to 
the company for medical treatments and lab tests that he never performed. 
</P>
<P>
 Although Shetty operated as a sole practitioner, the indictment alleges that 
he submitted claims using two separate provider numbers, one in his name and 
the other in the name of the Harbor Newport Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 If convicted, Shetty could be sentenced to a maximum of five years in prison 
and fined up to $250,000 on each of the 28 counts.GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
