<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: CENTERS OFFER FREE LUNCHES TO YOUTHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Free lunches are being served to youths at 17 recreational centers throughout 
the San Fernando Valley through Aug. 26, the Los Angeles Recreation and Parks 
Department has announced. 
</P>
<P>
 The federally funded meals program for people under 18 includes a sandwich, 
fruit, fruit juice and milk. 
</P>
<P>
 The lunches are aimed at youngsters who would be deprived of food assistance 
they would have during the school year, although all youths under 18 are 
eligible. 
</P>
<P>
 Serving times vary at each location. Contact the nearest center for exact 
times. 
</P>
<P>
 Participating recreation centers in the East Valley include Branford, 13310 
Branford St., Arleta; Fernangeles, 8851 Laurel Canyon Blvd., Sun Valley; 
Delano, 15100 Erwin St., Van Nuys; Hubert Humphrey, 12560 Filmore St., Pacoima; 
Lake View Terrace, 11075 Foothill Blvd., and North Hollywood, 11430 Chandler 
Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Others are North Weddington, 10844 Acama St., North Hollywood; Pacoima, 10943 
Herrick Ave.; Paxton, 10731 Laurel Canyon Blvd., Pacoima; Sepulveda, 8801 
Kester Ave., North Hills; Sun Valley, 8133 Vineland Ave.; Sunland, 8651 
Foothill Blvd.; Sylmar, 13109 Borden Ave.; Valley Plaza, 12240 Archwood St., 
North Hollywood; Van Nuys, 15401 Vanowen St., and Victory-Vineland, 11112 
Victory Blvd., North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 The only participating center in the West Valley is Lanark, 21816 Lanark St., 
Canoga Park. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
