VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: EXPLOSIVES FOUND IN CAR; 2 ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two youths were arrested Thursday after Los Angeles police discovered an 
explosive device in their car, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The unidentified boys, a 16-year-old Reseda resident and a 17-year-old from 
Northridge, were stopped by Los Angeles patrol officers, who found an explosive 
device and material for making other devices in the car, said Detective Steven 
Spear. 
</P>
<P>
 The youths later admitted detonating one device in a parking lot, Spear said. 
They led police to a house in the 8100 block of Etiwanda Street, where more 
material used to build the devices was confiscated. 
</P>
<P>
 The youths were booked at the Police Department's Devonshire Division on 
suspicion of possession of a destructive device in a public place, Spear said. 
</P>
<P>
 Spear said the confiscated device was less powerful than a pipe bomb, which is 
made with steel and, sometimes, plastic pipe and explosive materials. CHIP 
JOHNSON 
