<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; TRUCK OVERTURNS ON FREEWAY, SPILLING 30 
GALLONS OF FERTILIZER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A truck hauling fertilizer overturned on Henry Mayo Drive near the Golden 
State Freeway on Thursday morning, fouling the commute for motorists during 
rush hour, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 6:50 a.m., when the truck driver apparently lost 
control of the vehicle as it rounded a curve while traveling west on the 
two-lane state highway, CHP Officer Wendy Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 30 gallons of a fertilizer made from calcium ammonia nitrate spilled 
from the truck's trailer, authorities said.  
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles County Fire Department's Hazardous Materials Unit contained 
the spill on the roadway before it leaked into the sewer system, a Fire 
Department spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no injuries, and the road was reopened about 11:15 a.m, Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
 The CHP is investigating the accident, Moore said. 
</P>
